Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "novcu" in different forms and positions, with the starred word highlighted:

1. Želim da *novac* prebacim sa svog računa na tvoj. (I want to transfer *money* from my account to yours.)
2. Koliko *novca* si potrošio na tu haljinu? (How much *money* did you spend on that dress?)
3. Ona je dobila nagradu u *novcu*. (She received a prize in *money*.)
4. Neću da dam *novac* za ovaj proizvod jer je previše skup. (I won't give *money* for this product because it's too expensive.)
5. Zaista ne znam koliko *novca* imaš na računu. (I really don't know how much *money* you have in your account.)
6. Prijatelj mi je pozajmio *novac* kada sam bio u finansijskoj nevolji. (A friend lent me *money* when I was in financial trouble.)
7. Ovaj biznis je dobar na *novčanom* planu. (This business is good financially.)
8. Moj deda je imao *novčanik* pun novca. (My grandfather had a wallet full of money.)
9. Kada putujem, uvek nosim *novac* sa sobom. (When I travel, I always carry *money* with me.)
10. Kompanija je imala veliki *novčani* gubitak prošle godine. (The company had a large *monetary* loss last year.)

I hope this helps!